Project: Employee Data Analysis
Objective:
Analyze the given employee dataset to uncover trends and insights related to salary distribution, gender representation, department performance, and more.

Tasks:
Data Exploration:

Load the dataset using Pandas.
Check for missing values and handle them appropriately.
Convert any necessary columns to the correct data types.
Data Analysis:

Calculate the average salary for each department.
Analyze the distribution of bonuses across different departments.
Find the average age and salary for senior and non-senior employees.
Compare the average salary between genders.
Identify any correlation between age and salary.
Data Visualization:

Plot the distribution of salaries using a histogram.
Create a bar chart to compare average salaries across departments.
Use a pie chart to show the gender distribution within the company.
